    "spell": {
        "name": "Ring of Truth",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "You designate an area in which lies are revealed. Creatures in the area also take a \u20132 status penalty to Deception checks. Each time a creature in the area speaks a true statement, the soft ring of a bell sounds in the area. Creatures are aware of the magic; therefore, they can avoid answering questions to which they would normally respond with a lie, or they can be evasive as long as they remain within the boundaries of the truth. If a creature is in the area when the spell is cast or later enters the area, that creature attempts a Will save. It uses the results of this initial save if it leaves and reenters the area.",
        "subtype": "spell",
        "spell_type": "spell",
        "rank": 3,
